# .trivyignore — suppress known accepted-risk findings
# Format: <CVE-ID> or <Misconfiguration-ID>
# Each entry must have a comment explaining the business rationale.
# Review and update whenever dependencies change.

# ── IaC Misconfigurations ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# DS026 — No HEALTHCHECK instruction defined
# Reason: Health checks are managed externally by Render's platform health
#         probes and docker-compose healthcheck directives, not baked into
#         images. Adding HEALTHCHECK would duplicate and possibly conflict.
DS026

# ── admin/ CRA react-scripts ecosystem ───────────────────────────────────────
# The admin dashboard is a Create React App (CRA) static build.
# react-scripts pins transitive build-tool dependencies (nth-check, svgo,
# workbox, @svgr/*, css-select, serialize-javascript, etc.) that have known
# CVEs. These packages are webpack/build-time only — they are NOT included in
# the production static bundle served to browsers, and upgrading them requires
# a semver-major react-scripts bump (version 0.0.0 = eject).
# Mitigations: admin/ package manifests are excluded from the vuln scan via
# skip-files in ci.yml; only admin/Dockerfile is checked for IaC issues.
# These CVEs are accepted-risk for the build environment, not the runtime.
#
# nth-check ReDoS (GHSA-rp65-9cf3-cjxr)
CVE-2021-3803
# node-forge signature verification bypass
CVE-2022-24771
CVE-2022-24772
CVE-2022-24773
# underscore template injection
CVE-2021-23358
# svgo / css-select ReDoS chain
CVE-2022-37598
# path-to-regexp ReDoS
CVE-2024-45296
# picomatch ReDoS
CVE-2024-55565
# bfj polynomial expression DoS
CVE-2023-30798
# serialize-javascript XSS in serialised regexes
CVE-2020-7660
# jsonpath prototype pollution
CVE-2021-3805
